  <title>Week 4 Assignment</title>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Calculate the following limits. (15)
        <ol>
          <li><me>
            \lim_{x \rightarrow 3} \dfrac{x^2 - 2x - 3}{x^2 - 4x + 3}
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \lim_{x \rightarrow 2} \dfrac{x^2 - 2x - 3}{x^2 - 4x + 3}
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \lim_{x \rightarrow 2} \dfrac{\frac{4}{x} -
            \frac{8}{x^2}}{x^2 - 4}
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{x}{\sin^2 x} 
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{x^2 + 4}{x^2}
          </me></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For each of the following functions, find a value of <m>a</m>
        that makes the function continuous or demonstrate that no
        value of <m>a</m> is possible. (12)
        <ol>
          <li><me>
            f(x) = \Bigg\{ \begin{matrix}
              x^2 + ax \amp x \geq 2 \\
              x - 4 \amp x \lt 2
            \end{matrix}
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            f(x) = \Bigg\{ \begin{matrix}
              \ln (x-3) \amp x \leq 4 \\
              ax^2 + a \amp x \gt 4 
            \end{matrix}
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            f(x) = \Bigg\{ \begin{matrix}
              \sin (x + a) \amp x \gt 0 \\
              \cos (x + a) \amp x \leq 0 
            \end{matrix}
          </me></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>
